Impact

Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)

Session hijacking

Cookie theft (where applicable)

Account compromise

Arbitrary JavaScript execution

Client-side application manipulation

Remediation

Never render LLM output using unsafe DOM sinks such as innerHTML.

Sanitize or escape all model-generated content before displaying it.

Enforce a strict Content Security Policy (CSP).

Treat all LLM output as untrusted user input.

Use secure rendering methods such as textContent when displaying plain text.